        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 6:58PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 658 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Marionville, or near Aurora, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aurora, Mount Vernon, Marionville, Clever, Crane, Billings, Verona,
and Hurley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
